steve-b@access.digex.net (Steve Brinich) writes:
> > I assume that except for one-time pads, the NSA is much better at this
> >stuff than our adversaries. I can't prove it though, and if it's false, our
> >adversaries aren't going to tell us.

Minor aside: consider the application of the new CD-ROM writers to the
generation of one-time pads.  There may be a nice market for a dongle
that fits on a serial port and generates random bits (say, from a small
radioisotope source) and some software that writes it onto CD-ROMs.

Of course, the NSA probably already has a secret patent on it... (grin)


